==English==

===Etymology===
The word comes from the {{etyl|la}} ''[[desquamare]]'' meaning "to scrape the scales off a fish."

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{medical}} The [[shedding]] of the outer layers of the [[skin]]. For example, once the rash of  measles fades, there is desquamation.

